                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div>
                                        <div class="markdownMakeup max-w-full ">
                                            <p>There are two types of components: <strong>functional</strong> and
                                                <strong>class</strong> components. However, class components are not in
                                                use anymore, as React has shifted its focus towards functional
                                                components due to the introduction of React Hooks in version 16.8. Hooks
                                                allow developers to use state and other React features without the need
                                                for class components, which were previously the only way to create
                                                stateful components.</p>
                                            <p><strong>Class</strong> components relied on complex code involving the
                                                <strong>this</strong> keyword and lifecycle methods, making them more
                                                prone to bugs and harder to understand, especially for developers new to
                                                React. With the release of Hooks, functional components became more
                                                powerful and flexible, enabling developers to create stateful logic in a
                                                more straightforward and reusable way.
                                                Additionally, functional components are generally easier to
                                                <strong>read, test, and maintain, leading to a better developer</strong>
                                                experience. As a result, class components are now considered legacy, and
                                                the React team recommends using functional components with Hooks for all
                                                new code. Therefore, we are focusing only on functional components in
                                                this discussion.</p>
